<TITLE> Court frames charges against Nasim June 19 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 14 (bdnews24.com)  A special court Thursday deferred the date for framing charges against former telecoms minister Mohammad Nasim in the World Tel scam case for a fourth time . Judge Shahed Nuruddin of the Special Judge's Court-3 fixed June 19 to frame charges. The now-defunct Bureau of Anticorruption filed the case against Nasim and Consociates Limited director AHS Rahman on January 8, 2002. The case details have it that Nasim had cleared World Tel Holding Limited to set up 300,000 digital telephone lines without tender. AHS Rahman was an appointed consultant to the project. The date for framing charges had earlier been fixed for June 3 but special divisional judge Malik Abdullah Al-Mamun transferred the case to Special Judge's Court- 3 after fixing June 6 to frame charges. The date was against shifted to June 10 following an appeal by defence lawyers on June 6. The court later fixed June 14 because of absence of the lawyers. Nasim was taken to the court Thursday from Kashimpur jail. bdnews24
